seed_chunks:
Out here, the Salvagers’ Guild sells itself as a safety-and-ethics union, certifying crews and arbitrating claims; in truth it launders black-site wreckage and quietly erases manifests for the right patrons. Helix Meridian Consortium presents a clean corporate face—hazard pay, rescue beacons, “responsible reclamation”—while running a clandestine program to recover bio-tech prototypes that shouldn’t exist, paying the Guild to bury evidence. The Colonial Security Bureau claims jurisdictional oversight and anti-piracy enforcement, but its real work is containment: silencing witnesses, rewriting logs, and hunting survivors from the erased facility. Helix funds CSB task groups; CSB scapegoats Guild crews; the Guild feeds both sides selective coordinates, keeping the war profitable and the truth unfound.

```json
{
  "factions": [
    {
      "name": "Salvagers’ Guild",
      "public_front": "A worker-run safety and ethics union that certifies salvage crews and mediates claim disputes.",
      "hidden_agenda": "Launders black-site salvage, alters manifests, and sells deniable recoveries to the highest bidder."
    },
    {
      "name": "Helix Meridian Consortium",
      "public_front": "A reputable reclamation megacorp offering hazard pay, rescue infrastructure, and “responsible” salvage.",
      "hidden_agenda": "Recovers forbidden bio-tech prototypes and funds cover-ups to keep the program off-record."
    },
    {
      "name": "Colonial Security Bureau (CSB)",
      "public_front": "Government security authority providing anti-piracy enforcement and jurisdictional oversight.",
      "hidden_agenda": "Containment and narrative control: silencing witnesses, rewriting logs, and eliminating survivors tied to the erased facility."
    }
  ]
}
```

Cold-sector traffic is spiking: the Salvagers’ Guild has issued a “hazard moratorium” on the Kestrel Drift, even as it quietly auctions a set of black-site coordinates to select captains—bait for deniable recovery and a way to flush out witnesses. Helix Meridian’s recovery ship **Vigilant Bloom** is already inbound, broadcasting rescue protocols while running silent-boarder drills. Meanwhile, CSB Task Group **Pale Warrant** begins “anti-piracy sweeps,” seizing logs and detaining crews who crossed the Drift—one detainee is rumored to be a survivor from Mara’s erased evacuation, held under sedation and false charges.

```json
{
  "events": [
    {
      "name": "Kestrel Drift Moratorium & Black-Auction",
      "description": "The Salvagers’ Guild publicly declares a hazard moratorium around the Kestrel Drift while secretly auctioning black-site coordinates to favored crews. The move both monetizes deniable wreckage and lures out anyone hunting the erased facility’s trail.",
      "stakes": [
        "Opportunity to acquire coordinates tied to the erased operation",
        "Risk of Guild betrayal, altered manifests, and booby-trapped claims",
        "Salvage crews may turn on each other for access and payout"
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "CSB Task Group Pale Warrant Sweeps",
      "description": "CSB Task Group Pale Warrant conducts aggressive 'anti-piracy' inspections, confiscating nav data and detaining anyone with Drift proximity. Helix Meridian quietly supplies targeting intel while its ship Vigilant Bloom approaches under a humanitarian broadcast.",
      "stakes": [
        "Witnesses and survivors disappear into CSB custody",
        "Mara’s own record makes her vulnerable to detention or blackmail",
        "Helix may retrieve prototypes first, burying evidence permanently"
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

